Sandton’s newest development by Weinprop and Foresee Properties – aptly called HQ Sandton – will offer luxurious apartments at great prices. HQ Sandton is in the heart of Africa’s richest square mile and offers apartments that are much more affordable than most developments in the area. This makes it the perfect investment opportunity for first-time buyers or investors, especially those looking to get into the Sandton property market. Click here to learn more about HQ Sandton apartments. HQ Sandton offers a variety of apartments that are ideal for anyone who wants to live or invest in Sandton. The development is strategically placed on Katherine Street, where it is only a six-minute walk from the nearest Gautrain station, and is also near to the new Bus Rapid Transport system. This is complemented by its wide range of in-house facilities, which are spread across two floors – the ground floor and the eighth floor. On the ground floor, you can enjoy several restaurants that spill out onto an external deck and pool with awesome views, while many will also appreciate the 24-hour concierge service, concierge-type laundry service, gym, large swimming pool, and outdoor park with trails and a river. Moving up to the eighth floor takes you to one of the main attractions – the largest rooftop terrace in South Africa. This will feature its own swimming pool, bar area, restaurants, and will have a number of social areas that you can enjoy. When you’re not using the amenities offered by HQ Sandton, you’ll be relaxing in your luxurious apartment. HQ Sandton comprises 780 apartments of various sizes, including 32 square metre studio units, one-bedroom units up to 44 square metres, and two-bedroom units up to 63 square metres. The apartments are priced from as low as R990,000 – providing potential property buyers and investors an unprecedented opportunity to buy into Africa’s richest square mile. The apartments are also fully kitted out and feature a Eurocentric design thanks to Sketch Studio and their lead interior architect Enrike de Villiers. Key stakeholders in the development include: Weinprop – Developers
Foresee Properties – Developers
Messaris Wapenaar Cole Architects – Developers
Profica – Project Managers
